ds = xr.open_dataset("C:\WORK\Climate_data_analysis_ishmam\data/ERA5_2mtemp_total_precip_1979_2018_monthly.nc") #open the t2m + precipitation dataset

Basic info about the loaded dataset¶

1x1 degree resolution (Lat & Long)

Monthly data (1979 Jan to 2018 Dec - 480 months)

Variables :

Total monthly prec (m)

Temperature (K)

In [8]:
grouped = grouped - 273.15
grouped.sel(month = 1).plot(label = 'January', color = 'c', linestyle = '--')
grouped.sel(month = 7).plot(label = 'July', color = 'r', linestyle = '--')
grouped.mean(dim = 'month').plot(label = 'Annual Avg', linewidth=3, color = 'g')

ax = plt.axes(projection=ccrs.Robinson())

(t2m_time_avg - 273.15).plot(ax = ax, transform=ccrs.PlateCarree(), levels = 7, vmin = -30, vmax = 30, cmap = 'inferno') 
plt.title('Mean Temperature (1979 -2018)')

ax.coastlines(); ax.gridlines(); # Add gridlines and coastlines to the plot

Realistic representation of North and South Pole (Change Projection system)¶

In [11]:
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(9, 7))
ax = plt.axes(projection=ccrs.NorthPolarStereo())
ax.set_extent([-180, 180, 90, 60], ccrs.PlateCarree())
(t2m_time_avg - 273.15).plot(ax=ax, transform=ccrs.PlateCarree()) 
plt.title('Mean Temperature (1979 -2018) - Regions near North Pole')
ax.coastlines();
ax.gridlines(draw_labels = True);

Change Projection System for Europe¶

In [13]:
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(9, 7))
ax = plt.axes(projection=ccrs.EuroPP())
(t2m_time_avg - 273.15).plot(ax=ax, transform=ccrs.PlateCarree(), vmin = 20, vmax = 30, cmap = 'coolwarm' )
plt.title('Mean Temperature (1979 -2018)- Europe')
ax.add_feature(cartopy.feature.BORDERS)
ax.coastlines() 
grid = ax.gridlines(draw_labels = True)
grid.ylabels_right = False;
grid.xlabels_bottom = False; # turn off bottom and right labeling

  • precipitation data: blues, YlGnBu work quite good

  • terrain heights: terain

  • temperature: inferno, hot_r, coolwarm

  • wind data: e.g. cool

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(16, 16)) #define a figure of a certain size
ax = plt.subplot(2, 2, 1, projection=ccrs.PlateCarree()) #first subplot
africa_temp_djf.plot.contourf(ax=ax, transform=ccrs.PlateCarree(),levels=np.arange(5, 45, 3), cmap='hot_r', 
                              cbar_kwargs={'label':'[°C]'})
# the actual plot with levels, a colormap and a labeled colorbar
ax.coastlines(); #add coastlines
xl = ax.gridlines(draw_labels=True); #add gridlines with labels
xl.xlabels_top = False # no labels at the top
xl.ylabels_right = False # no labels on the right side
ax.add_feature(cartopy.feature.BORDERS, linestyle='--'); # add dashed country borders
ax.set_title('Average T        DJF'); # add a title

ax = plt.subplot(2, 2, 2, projection=ccrs.PlateCarree())
africa_temp_mam.plot.contourf(ax=ax, transform=ccrs.PlateCarree(),levels=np.arange(5, 43, 3), cmap='hot_r', cbar_kwargs={'label':'[°C]'})
ax.coastlines();
xl = ax.gridlines(draw_labels=True);
xl.xlabels_top = False
xl.ylabels_right = False
ax.add_feature(cartopy.feature.BORDERS, linestyle='--');
ax.set_title('Average T        MAM');
